  "title": "Magnetic flux - flux through hemisphere",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a hollow hemisphere with radius R that is oriented such that its diameter is vertically aligned, and a horizontal line drawn from its center to the top of the hemisphere would point to the right. A magnetic field B is indicated that points upward and to right, such that it makes an angle theta with the horizontal.\" src=\"/images/637c64377f59579eb5ad5e92903e523a.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A region of space has a hollow hemisphere of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>. A uniform magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> passes through the hemisphere at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> as shown. Which of the following correctly describes the magnetic flux through the curved surface of the hemisphere?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The net flux through the curved surface is zero.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The flux through the curved surface can only be found by integrating <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the contour integral of vector B dot d vector A\"><math alttext=\"the contour integral of vector B dot d vector A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>∮</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>·</mo><mi>d</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mstyle></math></span></span> over the curved area.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The amount of flux out of the curved surface is equal to the amount of flux into the left circular face of the hemisphere.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The flux through the surface is the same no matter the orientation of the hemisphere.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
